The article is a statement by the President on the Senate passage of the 21st Century Cures Act. The President highlights that this bipartisan act will help in ending cancer, finding cures for diseases like Alzheimer's, and providing treatment for opioid addiction. The act includes investments of $1 billion to address the opioid epidemic, $1.8 billion for cancer research, and nearly $3 billion for biomedical research initiatives. It also focuses on improving mental health and enhancing the drug development process. The President emphasizes the importance of working together to improve the health of families and communities.